snippet.textDisplay:
"Steals the game from Rangers"... eh what?

Rangers NEVER looked in control of that game. Not even when they went a goal up!
Only chances they got were on the break because Hearts were playing a high defensive line and had them penned in all game. They had no shape, no gameplan and no real answer for Hearts. Gerrard even admitted it himself.

Hearts dominated possession and created more chances. They won this game on their own merit for playing the way they did. They'll climb up to safety if they can play like that every week and they'll definitely win more than they lose. All credit to Stendel, his new signings and the improvements and confidence he's made to once maligned players like Sean Clare.

Shameful levels of bias and favouritism. But I guess that's nothing new, eh? Anything for the precious rangers.
